--- body ---
## Context

`run_l2_permutations` in `scripts/_permutation_lexical.py` iterates over
`(year, window)` pairs in a single-threaded loop.  On the full corpus
(~30k works, w=3 and w=5, ~50 pairs) this takes ~90 minutes.  Every other
null model driver uses `n_jobs` to saturate available cores.  Three places
need updating: the function itself, the dispatcher shim, and the Makefile
recipe.

L3 is already fast (it permutes a length-25 array n_perm times using
numpy — no per-window loop) and does not need this fix.

## Relevant files

- `scripts/_permutation_lexical.py:111` — `run_l2_permutations` — outer
  loop over `(year, window)` pairs; per-window logic is a closure
  `_resonance_from_split` that captures `X_all` and `year_vecs`
- `scripts/compute_null_model.py:346` — `_run_l2_permutations` — thin
  shim; does not accept `n_jobs`; compare the semantic/citation shims
  which do
- `scripts/compute_null_model.py:796` — dispatcher call site — passes no
  `n_jobs`; compare L769 (citation) and L791 (semantic)
- `divergence.mk:220` — L2/L3 Makefile recipe — missing `--n-jobs
  $(NJOBS)`; compare semantic/citation recipes which include it

## Actions

1. In `_permutation_lexical.py`, add `n_jobs=1` parameter to
   `run_l2_permutations`.  Extract the per-window body into a
   module-level (picklable) helper — e.g.
   `_compute_l2_window(y, w, X_all, doc_years, n_past, pool_indices, year_vecs, n_perm, seed)`.
   Replace the `for` loop with `joblib.Parallel(n_jobs=n_jobs)(delayed(...)
   for ...)` when `n_jobs != 1`, keeping the sequential path for `n_jobs=1`.

2. In `compute_null_model.py`, update `_run_l2_permutations(div_df, cfg)`
   to `_run_l2_permutations(div_df, cfg, n_jobs=1)` and forward to
   `run_l2_permutations(..., n_jobs=n_jobs)`.

3. In `compute_null_model.py`, update the dispatcher call at line ~797:
   ```python
   result = _run_l2_permutations(div_df, cfg, n_jobs=args.n_jobs)
   ```

4. In `divergence.mk`, add `--n-jobs $(NJOBS)` to the L2L3 recipe (the
   `NULL_METHODS_LEX_L2L3` block).

## Test

Red: add a test to `tests/test_null_model_lexical.py` (or the nearest
equivalent) that calls `run_l2_permutations(..., n_jobs=2)` on a tiny
synthetic corpus (3 years, 10 docs each) and asserts the result has the
same columns and row count as `n_jobs=1`.

## Verification

- [ ] `run_l2_permutations(div_df, cfg, n_jobs=2)` returns identical
  schema to `n_jobs=1` on the test fixture
- [ ] `make -j4 NJOBS=6 null-model` re-runs L2 and completes in < 15 min
  on padme (vs ~90 min single-threaded)
- [ ] `make check-fast` passes (no pre-existing failures introduced)

## Invariants

- L3 must not be touched (already fast; different algorithm)
- Sequential path (`n_jobs=1`) must produce bit-identical output to the
  current implementation
- The L2L3 Makefile recipe change must not break L3 (L3 ignores
  `--n-jobs` — verify the dispatcher silently passes it through or guards)

## Exit criteria

- New test is green
- `make check-fast` clean
- PR merged to main
